<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFF33FF5AFEAF440D" box="[189,262,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Notes:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFE88FF5BFE8B440D" bold="true" box="[262,290,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">—</emphasis>
Two isolates from air clustered into a well 
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFCB7FF5BFCEB440D" bold="true" box="[825,834,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">-</emphasis>
supported clade (
<figureCitation id="C4806287FFFFFF9DFB9AFF5BFBF7440D" box="[1044,1118,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1717,1739]" captionTargetBox="[227,1349,571,1648]" captionTargetId="figure-194@3.[227,1361,555,1662]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1—Phylogenetic tree from maximum parsimony analysis based on a combined of ITS and LSU gene sequences. Numbers above the nodes indicate MP bootstrap proportion (left, MPBP ≥ 50%), Maximum Likelihood bootstrap proportion (medium, MLBP ≥ 50%) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (right, BPP ≥ 0.9). Isolates from present study are in blue. Scale bar = 20 nucleotide." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6503888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6503888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="9BBB0581FFFFFF9DFBF1FF5BFA21440D" authorityName="Wang &amp; Jiang &amp; Tu &amp; Zhu &amp; Xue &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[1151,1416,230,256]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Saccotheciaceae" genus="Aureobasidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Dothideales" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aerium">
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFBF1FF5BFA21440D" box="[1151,1416,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Aureobasidium aerium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="9BBB0581FFFFFF9DFE3EFEB7FD4F4429" box="[432,742,266,292]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Saccotheciaceae" genus="Aureobasidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Dothideales" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subglaciale">
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFE3EFEB7FD4F4429" box="[432,742,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Aureobasidium subglaciale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from subglacial ice in sea water; 
<taxonomicName id="9BBB0581FFFFFF9DFBF8FEB7FA024429" box="[1142,1451,266,292]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Saccotheciaceae" genus="Aureobasidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Dothideales" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucosperm">
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFBF8FEB7FA024429" box="[1142,1451,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Aureobasidium leucosperm</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="9BBB0581FFFFFF9DFF46FE92FEDA4445" box="[200,371,303,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Proteaceae" genus="Leucospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ECFA210FFFFFF9DFF46FE92FEDA4445" box="[200,371,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Leucospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
